The Provincial Information Officer. â

No person shall be appointed information officer unless he is a citizen of the Philippines, a resident of the province, of good moral character, a holder of a college degree preferably in journalism, mass communications or any related course from a recognized college or university, and a first grade civil service eligible or its equivalent. He must have acquired experience in writing articles and research papers, or in writing for print, television or broadcast media for at least three years.

